    "shortDesc": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with diabetic cataract",
    "longDesc": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with diabetic cataract",
    "plainEnglish": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with diabetic cataract means a person has high blood sugar (type 2 diabetes) and has developed clouding of the lens in their eye as a complication of diabetes. This cloudiness causes blurry or dim vision and develops when high blood sugar levels over time damage the proteins in the eye lens, making it increasingly difficult to see clearly.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, primary care physicians, and ophthalmologists use this code when managing diabetic patients who have developed cataracts as a diabetes complication. It commonly appears on EOB statements for diabetic patients undergoing eye exams, cataract surgery consultations, or treatment for vision problems related to their diabetes.",
    "billable": true,
    "isNew": false,
    "isRevised": false,
