    "longDesc": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with hyperglycemia",
    "plainEnglish": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with hyperglycemia means your body either doesn't make enough insulin or can't use the insulin it makes effectively, causing your blood sugar to be abnormally high. This is the most common type of diabetes and often develops gradually due to factors like obesity, physical inactivity, or aging. You may experience symptoms like increased thirst, frequent urination, fatigue, or blurred vision.",
