    "shortDesc": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus without complications",
    "longDesc": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus without complications",
    "plainEnglish": "Type 2 diabetes is a condition where your body either doesn't make enough insulin or can't use the insulin it makes effectively, causing blood sugar levels to stay too high. This code specifically describes someone with type 2 diabetes who currently has no major complications like kidney disease, eye damage, or nerve damage—though they may develop these issues later if their blood sugar isn't controlled. It's the most common form of diabetes and is often related to weight, age, and family history.",
