    "longDesc": "Vitamin D deficiency, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "Vitamin D deficiency means your body doesn't have enough vitamin D, a nutrient that helps your bones absorb calcium and keeps your immune system strong. This can happen from not getting enough sunlight, not eating foods rich in vitamin D, or your body having trouble absorbing it. You might feel tired, have muscle aches, or notice your bones feel weak, though many people with low vitamin D have no symptoms at all.",
